      "side": 1,
      "message": "ha, since I was reviewing your CL  bottom -\u003e up,\nI\u0027ve just wrote similar concern about CLUpdated event and suggested to either not consume event or record event for later processing inside RM.state.\n\nWhat you do here is #3 approach -- consume \u0026\u0026 but re-insert the same event.\nThis has some downsides:\n * more DS mutation churn\n * creates more kick/poke RM tasks\n   -\u003e can be addressed by using eventbox.Add directly\nbut major upside:\n * it\u0027s simpler than 2 other alternatives.\n\nI don\u0027t know which one is better. I\u0027m OK starting with this one.",
